headline.main: Sweet Potato Diet of Papuans a Nutritional Puzzle

byline.original: By JOHN A. OSMUNDSEN Special to The New York Times

docs.abstract: Dr Oomen studies ability of New Guinea Papuans to subsist on diet almost entirely of sweet potatoes
docs.lead_paragraph: AMSTERDAM, the Netherlands, Sept. 13--An authority on human nutrition here is trying to figure out how natives in the highlands of western New Guinea can get along on the most unbalanced diet in the world.
